  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition 3 of planning permission ref P2018/3467/FUL is amended as follows: \r\n\r\nNO OBSCURING OF SHOPFRONTS (COMPLIANCE): With the exception of the areas indicated on the approved drawings (no's LAD-00-GF-DR-Y-111 Rev P3; Dwg LAD-00-XX-DR-Y-905 P3; Dwg LAD-00-XX-DR-Y-906 P3) the window glass of all ground floor commercial units shall not be painted, tinted or otherwise obscured and no furniture or fixings which may obscure visibility above a height of 1.4m above finished floor level be placed within 2.0m of the inside of the window glass. Furthermore, the artwork hereby approved on the areas with a manifestation shall not be changed without the prior written consent of the local planning authority. \r\n\r\nREASON: In the interest of securing passive surveillance of the street, an appropriate street frontage appearance and preventing the creation of dead/inactive frontages."
